radiographic_examinations.findings: Minimal atelectasis in bilateral lung bases; Appendix is filled with fluid and enlarged up to diameter of 15 mm with a 15 x 6 mm hyperdense structure possibly an obstructing appendicolith. Surrounding fat stranding noted. No evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion, intrahepatic or extrahepatic biliary dilatation, focal lesions in pancreas, spleen, or kidneys.
